		      		<hr>
              Since Fall 2015, I have moved to The University of Dayton as a faculty member. My current homepage is on <a href="http://academic.udayton.edu/PhuPhung">http://academic.udayton.edu/PhuPhung</a> (You will be redirected to the page in 10 seconds).  
              <hr>
					   <h3>Research</h3>
             <blockquote>
							My current research mainly focuses on software security, with use of ideas from programming languages, reference monitors, and compilers to defeat potential malicious behaviors from untrusted software. Some highlights of my publications:
              <ul>
              <li> Defensive Optimizing Compilation: <a href="research/publications_abstracts.html#Gjomemo+:VMCAI:2015">VMCAI'15</a>.  
              <li> Cross-Language Web Protection: <a href="research/publications_abstracts.html#Phung+:TDSC:2014">TDSC'2014 (to appear)</a>.

              <li> JavaScript Sandboxing: <a href="http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-41488-6_5">NordSec'13</a>, <a href="http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2420952">ACSAC'12</a>, <a href="http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=2307721">JSTools'12</a>.</li> 
              <li> Policy enforcement for Bot-as-a-Service: <a href="http://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1877050912004292">MobiWIS'12</a>.</li>
              <li> Self-Protecting JavaScript: <a href="http://dl.acm.org/citation.cfm?id=1533067">ASIACCS'09</a>, <a href="http://link.springer.com/chapter/10.1007/978-3-642-27937-9_17">AppSec Research'10</a>.</li>
              
              <li> Securing untrusted vehicle applications: <a href="http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpls/abs_all.jsp?arnumber=4591725">COMPSAC'08</a>, <a href="http://ieeexplore.ieee.org/xpls/abs_all.jsp?arnumber=5549229">RTIC'10</a>.</li>
              </ul>
              
              <b>Publications</b>
                <ul>
                  <li>On <a href="http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=3VspJzMAAAAJ">Google Scholar</a>. 
