              <b>Current projects</b>
                <ul>
                  <li>interWebSec: Cross-Language Web Protection, 2013-2016, funded by the <a href="http://www.vr.se/" target="_blank">Swedish Research Council (VR)</a>, PI: Phu Phung. 
                  </li>
                  <li>Securing Web Advertisements, 2011-2013, funded by <a href="http://www.nsf.gov/" target="_blank">NSF</a>, PIs: <a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~venkat/" target="_blank">V.N. Venkat</a> (UIC), and <a href="http://www.utdallas.edu/~hamlen/" target="_blank">Kevin W. Hamlen</a> (UTD) . 
                  </li>
                  <li>Defensive Optimizing Compilation, 2012-2015, funded by <a href="http://www.darpa.mil/Our_Work/I2O/Programs/Crowd_Sourced_Formal_Verification_(CSFV).aspx" target="_blank">DARPA</a>, PIs: <a href="http://www.cs.ucla.edu/~palsberg/" target="_blank">Jens Palsberg</a> (UCLA), <a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~venkat/" target="_blank">V.N. Venkat</a> (UIC), <a href="http://www.cs.uic.edu/~lenore/" target="_blank">Lenore D. Zuck</a> (UIC), and <a href="http://ect.bell-labs.com/who/knamjoshi/" target="_blank">Kedar Namjoshi</a> (Bell Labs, Alcatel-Lucent).
                  </li>
                </ul>
              <b>Past projects</b>
                <ul>
                  <li>WebSand: Server-driven Outbound Web-application Sandboxing, <a href="https://www.websand.eu/" target="_blank">https://www.websand.eu/</a>  
                  </li>
                  <li>SESAME: Security for Extensible Software Architectures in Mobile Environments, funded by <a href="http://www.vinnova.se/en/" target="_blank">the Swedish Governmental Agency for Innovation Systems (VINNOVA)</a>, in collaboration with <a href="http://www.volvo.com/" target="_blank">Volvo Technology</a>.
